{"parse":{"title":"Blue Ear","pageid":35930379,"revid":839637842,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"width:22em;width: 24em; background: #f2f9ff;\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #99c2ff;\">Blue Ear</th></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background: #99c2ff;\">Publication information</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Category:Comics_publishing_companies\" title=\"Category:Comics publishing companies\">Publisher</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Marvel_Comics\" title=\"Marvel Comics\">Marvel Comics</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/First_appearance\" title=\"First appearance\">First appearance</a></th><td>\n<i>Iron Man: Sound Effects</i> #1 (December 2014)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Category:Comics_creators\" title=\"Category:Comics creators\">Created by</a></th><td>\nNelson Ribeiro</td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background: #99c2ff;\">In-story information</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">Alter ego</th><td>\nDr. Pedro Perez</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">Abilities</th><td>\nExpert physicist<br />Sound manipulation</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Blue Ear</b> is a fictional <a href=\"/wiki/Superhero\" title=\"Superhero\">superhero</a> appearing in <a href=\"/wiki/American_comic_book\" title=\"American comic book\">American comic books</a> published by <a href=\"/wiki/Marvel_Comics\" title=\"Marvel Comics\">Marvel Comics</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Marvel created the character in honor of Anthony Smith, a <a href=\"/wiki/Deafness\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Deafness\">hard-of-hearing</a> 4-year-old comic book fan from <a href=\"/wiki/Salem,_New_Hampshire\" title=\"Salem, New Hampshire\">Salem</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/New_Hampshire\" title=\"New Hampshire\">New Hampshire</a>, USA.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Smith has no hearing in his right ear and minimal hearing in his left because he has Mosaic <a href=\"/wiki/Trisomy_22\" title=\"Trisomy 22\">trisomy 22</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publication_history\">Publication history</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Blue_Ear&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Publication history\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Smith was given a <a href=\"/wiki/Hearing_aid\" title=\"Hearing aid\">hearing aid</a> by his mother, Christina D'Allesandro, and was using it regularly until he became depressed and refused to wear it to school in 2012. According to Smith, \"superheroes don't wear blue ears\". D'Allesandro was alarmed by this and emailed Marvel Comics in <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_City\" title=\"New York City\">New York City</a> for assistance with the situation. Designer and assistant editor, Nelson Ribeiro, then created the original image of the Blue Ear<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and sent it to the D'Allesandro family. Later, production artist <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Manny_Mederos&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Manny Mederos (page does not exist)\">Manny Mederos</a> started working on a sketch of Blue Ear as a kid. Mederos told <i><a href=\"/wiki/Huffington_Post\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Huffington Post\">Huffington Post</a></i> that during the creative process, Mederos had an idea: \"Why not have the superhero be a young kid himself?\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Marvel Comics responded by sending D'Allesandro comics of <a href=\"/wiki/Hawkeye_(comics)\" title=\"Hawkeye (comics)\">Hawkeye</a> from the 1980s, when the superhero lost 80% of his hearing and had to wear hearing aids, along with a drawing of \"The Blue Ear\", a superhero based on Anthony, saying, \"Thanks to my listening device I hear someone in trouble!\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>D'Allesandro stated that Smith took the comic book pictures to his preschool, which pushed teachers to have a \"superhero week\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> Smith's grandfather, New Hampshire senator <a href=\"/wiki/Lou_D%27Allesandro\" title=\"Lou D&#39;Allesandro\">Lou D'Allesandro</a>, stated, \"This is a feel good moment, it's a feel good story, and we've got to get the world to recognize that.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> In March 2013, Smith attended an event at the Center for Hearing and Communication to debut a poster.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Blue Ear character returned for his comic debut in a Team-up Marvel Custom Solutions Iron Man Issue, along with the titular Iron Man &amp; new character named Sapheara, for another campaign for deaf kids. Under the costumes based on Nelson Ribeiro's design, Blue Ear this time was written under the name 'Dr. Pedro Perez', &amp; was given an origin for his heroic identity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> Blue Ear returns with Sapheara under a four-part, one-page 'Limited Comic Strip Series' called <i>Blue Ear &amp; Sapheara</i> in celebration for Better Hearing &amp; Speech Month.<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Blue_Ear&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Sign_Gene\" title=\"Sign Gene\">Sign Gene</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Blue_Ear&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Hanson, Julie (May 26, 2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.unionleader.com/article/20120526/NEWS/705269948\">\"Superheroes do wear blue ears, thanks to NH boy\"</a>. <i>The Union Leader</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">May 27,</span> 2012</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Union+Leader&amp;rft.atitle=Superheroes+do+wear+blue+ears%2C+thanks+to+NH+boy&amp;rft.date=2012-05-26&amp;rft.aulast=Hanson&amp;rft.aufirst=Julie&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.unionleader.com%2Farticle%2F20120526%2FNEWS%2F705269948&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlue+Ear\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note